title: Design an eye catching logo for an electronic version of high school yearbooks
description: Recapp is the next generation of high school yearbooks. Recapp is a website and mobile application that allows high school students to convert their typical "printing-press" style yearbook into a digital, interactive, and updated version of their high school experience. The students can add video clips from their homecoming sporting events, band/choir performances, etc. The students will be able to record their senior quotes as audio files and put their actual signatures via stylus or touch screen into the back of each others new "yearbooks." Recapp also stores previous yearbooks within its data base to ensure each student can access their new digital yearbooks whenever and wherever they want. Students can store their freshman, sophomore, junior, and senior yearbooks all within their Recapp profile page and access them individually with the tap of their finger. Students will be able to show their future families their high school experiences in vivid detail with videos, pictures, audio files, and unique signatures. High schoolers and their parents are the target audience, but you may feel free to be as creative as you would like to be with this logo. "Recapp" is a play on words for "cap and gown" while also referencing the idea of a yearbook being a "summary/recap" of the school year and, like the word "yearbook," it ends with the word "app" rather than "book" since it is a mobile application rather than a physical book.

title: Design a logo for a Texas-based conservation/environmental organization
description:
The Bandera Canyonland Alliance (http://www.banderacanyonlandalliance.com) is a Texas-based 501(c)3 nonprofit charitable organization that was formed to protect and preserve the ecological systems that support the biodiversity, water resources, natural beauty and rural way of life in the Bandera Canyonlands.
The Bandera Canyonlands region is located along the southwest edge of the Edwards Plateau of Central Texas and is an ecologically significant area. Springs and rivers located in the canyons support several unique plant and animal communities and provide water supply for livestock and wildlife. Property in this area is highly desirable and its many parks are visited by thousands of tourists every year.
BCA members are local citizens who work cooperatively with the community, landowners, ranchers, conservationists, developers, and elected officials to preserve the water quality, water supply and natural beauty of the area. Members believe that a strong economic and sustainable future for this region will depend on the ability to balance growth with the conservation of the very resources that makes this area such a treasured place to live.
Two ongoing programs of the BCA are land management and feral hog management (HOGMOP), however, the BCA is actively involved in other initiatives to preserve the integrity of the land and the pure waters of the region.

title: Distinctive logo for an antenna brand
description: We manufacture antennas and accessories for handheld walkie-talkies and for vehicles.
other_notes:
The logo will be applied to our antennas for walkie talkies and vehicles. Antennas are often small, so the logo should be rectangular (horizontal) look good and distinctive even in small areas.
We are interested in the idea of using a distinctive primary color for the logo that we could also incorporate into the product (example: neon green logo text and matching color top cap on the antenna.)
Our products are generally a single solid color, 80% are black and ~15% will be white. The logo will need to look good on both white and black backgrounds, or we will need a variation for each.
We need the following variations to the primary logo:
- Square variation
- Variation for white and black background
I am attaching examples of some products that are similar to what we will be selling.
